Federal_Way.French Field (Kent, Washington): French Field is a multi-purpose stadium in Kent, Washington, United States. It is a stadium for high school teams in the area including Kent-Meridian High School, Kentlake High School, Kentridge High School and Kentwood High School football, soccer and track teams. It is also home for The Seattle Majestics, a professional Women's American football team in the Women's Football Alliance and was home to The King County Jaguars, a semi-professional American football team in the North American Football League.
